We had lunch here the other day and really enjoyed it. My favorite was the veggie gau (like a goyoza but better). The cucumber dish and the rice noodles were also good, as were the veggie dumplings.  My husband got a pork bun, pork dumplings,  and a soup and enjoyed them as well. We ordered way too much food and couldn't finish it but it was very good and we both would like to go back.
